flagicon|ZAF}})\n|date=1 October 2016\n|home={{ru-rt|ARG}}\n|score=17 - 36\n|away={{Ru|NZL}}\n|stadium = }}\n|-\n|{{Rugbybox |report= \n|referee=([[Jaco Peyper]] {{flagicon|ZAF}})\n|date=30 September 2017\n|home={{ru-rt|ARG}}\n|score=10 - 36\n|away={{Ru|NZL}}\n|stadium =}}\n|-\n|{{Rugbybox |report= \n|referee=([[Mathieu Raynal]] {{flagicon|FRA}})\n|date=29 September 2018\n|home={{ru-rt|ARG}}\n|score=17 - 35\n|away={{Ru|NZL}}\n|stadium = }}\n|-\n|{{Rugbybox |report= \n|referee=([[Angus Gardner]] {{flagicon|AUS}})\n|date=21 July 2019\n|home={{ru-rt|ARG}}\n|score=16 - 20\n|away={{Ru|NZL}}\n|stadium = }}\n|}\n\n==Concerts==\n[[File:Queen maradona.jpg|thumb|right|[[Queen (band)|Queen]] (with singer [[Freddie Mercury]] in an [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] jersey) in a meeting with [[Diego Maradona]] before their last concert at V\u00e9lez Sarsfield, 8 March 1981]]\nThe stadium has hosted many international concerts since the 1980s. [[England|English]] [[rock music|rock]] [[band (rock and pop)|band]] [[Queen (band)|Queen]] was the first to perform at V\u00e9lez Sarsfield \u2013giving three concerts in February 1981\u2013 as part of [[The Game Tour]] to support their successful [[The Game (Queen album)|homonymous album]].<ref>[https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/la-leyenda-de-queen-en-argentina-nid1066163 La leyenda de Queen en Argentina], ''Rolling Stone'', 5 Nov 2008</ref> The visit of the band (which was at the peak of their career by then) had huge repercussions in Argentina, being widely covered by the media, and famous personalities \u2013such as [[Diego Maradona]]\u2013 attending to their concerts.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/teleshow/infoshow/2018/11/18/los-agitados-dias-de-queen-en-la-argentina-secretos-detras-de-los-shows-el-encuentro-con-maradona-y-un-desengano-amoroso-para-freddie-mercury/ Los agitados d\u00edas de Queen en la Argentina] by Mat\u00edas Bauzo on Infobae, 17 Nov 2018</ref><ref>[https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/la-historia-detras-foto-diego-maradona-freddie-nid2186732 La historia detr\u00e1s de la foto] by Pablo Lisotto, ''La Naci\u00f3n'', 30 Oct 2018</ref>\n\nJos\u00e9 Amalfitani hosts events of up to 50,000 spectators.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed sortable\" style=\"width:800px\"\n|-\n! colspan=4| Concerts hosted at Jos\u00e9 Amalfitani Stadium\n|-\n! width=200px| Artist\n! width=300px| Date\n! width=300px| Tour\n|-\n| [[Queen (band)|Queen]] || February 28,March 1 and 8,1981 || [[The Game Tour]]\n|-\n| [[Yes (band)|Yes]] || February 1, 2 and 8,1984 || [[List of Yes concert tours (1980s\u201390s)#9012Live Tour|9012Live Tour]]\n|-\n| [[Tears for Fears]] || January 23, 1990 || Seeds of Love\n|-\n| [[Bon Jovi]] || February 1, 1990 ||[[New Jersey Syndicate Tour]]\n|-\n| [[Erasure]] || March 31, 1990 || Wild! Tour\n|-\n| [[Roxette]] || May 2 and 3, 1992 || [[Join the Joyride! Tour]]\n|-\n| [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]] || October 30, 1992 || [[Nevermind]] Tour\n|-\n| [[Joe Cocker]] and [[Brian May]] || November 7, 1992 || \n|-\n| [[The B-52's]] || November 8, 1992 || \n|-\n| [[Duran Duran]] ||April 30, 1993 || 1993-1994 The Dilate Your Mind Tour\n|-\n| [[Metallica]] ||May 7 and 8, 1993 || [[Nowhere Else to Roam]]\n|-\n| [[Santana (band)|Santana]] || May 29, 1993|| Milagro Tour\n|-\n| [[Peter Gabriel]] || October 2, 1993|| Secret World Tour\n|-\n| [[Bon Jovi]] || November 12, 13 and 14, 1993 ||[[I'll Sleep When I'm Dead Tour]]\n|-\n|[[Luis Miguel]]||November 19, 1993||[[Aries Tour]]\n|-\n| [[Aerosmith]] || January 17, 1994|| [[Get a Grip Tour]]\n|-\n| [[INXS]] || March 4, 1994|| Dirty Honeymoon Tour\n|-\n| [[Sting (musician)|Sting]] || March 25, 1994|| Ten Summoner's Tales Tour\n|-\n| [[Depeche Mode]]||April 8, 1994||[[Exotic Tour/Summer Tour '94]]\n|-\n| [[Whitney Houston]]|| April 16 and 17, 1994 || [[The Bodyguard World Tour]]\n|-\n|[[Ramones]]||May 14, 1994|| 20th Anniversary Tour\n|-\n|[[Luis Miguel]]||November 11& 12, 1994||[[Segundo Romance Tour]]\n|-\n|[[Testamen